gh evidence to take the case to court. </p>\n\n<p>If the <abbr title=\"Crown Prosecution Service\">CPS</abbr> decide to drop or alter the charge, they must tell you within 5 days.</p>\n\n<h2>Victim personal statement</h2>\n\n<p>You can tell the police how the crime has affected you. This is called a &lsquo;victim personal statement&rsquo;. It can be used later when the court is deciding on a punishment.</p>\n\n<h2>Privacy</h2>\n\n<p>The police might give some information about the crime to the media to help with the investigation. They&rsquo;ll normally ask your permission before they do this.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;ve been the victim of a sexual assault or rape, it&rsquo;s against the law for anyone to publish your name, photo or anything else that could identify you.</p>\n\n<h2>Victim support</h2>\n\n<p>Victim Support is a charity that can offer you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>emotional support to help you cope with the effects of crime</li>\n  <li>practical help, eg improving home security or with filling in forms for insurance and compensation</li>\n  <li>advice on dealing with the police</li>\n  <li>information and support if you have to go to court as a witness</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Visit the Victim Support website or call their helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Victim Support</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://www.victimsupport.org.uk\" title=\"Victim Support\" rel=\"external\">www.victimsupport.org.uk</a><br />\n0845 30 30 900</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can also <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://victimservices.justice.gov.uk/\" title=\"Search for victim support services on the Justice website\">find victim services in your area</a> that can help you.</p>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re contacted by a prisoner</h2>\n\n<p>If you get unwanted letters, phone calls, texts or messages from a prisoner, contact the National Offender Management Service (<abbr title=\"National Offender Management Service\">NOMS</abbr>) Victim Helpline.</p>\n\n<p>You can also contact the helpline if you&rsquo;re worried about someone being released from prison.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"National Offender Management Service\">NOMS</abbr> Victim Helpline</strong><br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#118;&#105;&#099;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#046;&#104;&#101;&#108;&#112;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#101;&#064;&#110;&#111;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#118;&#105;&#099;&#116;&#105;&#109;&#046;&#104;&#101;&#108;&#112;&#108;&#105;&#110;&#101;&#064;&#110;&#111;&#109;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n0845 7585 112</p>\n</div>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Reporting crimes and getting compensation","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Freporting-crimes-compensation.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including criminal injuries compensation and reporting suspected crimes","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Freporting-crimes-compensation","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/reporting-crimes-compensation"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/going-to-court-victim-witness.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/going-to-court-victim-witness","title":"Going to court as a victim or witness","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:15:14+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/claim-compensation-criminal-injury.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/claim-compensation-criminal-injury","title":"Claim compensation for a criminal injury","format":"transaction","upd